title: fasces_(object)
body:
[B]Fasces[/b] is an object or [[heraldry|heraldic]] symbol that consists of a bound wooden rod bundle, often incorporating an axe (occasionally two) with its blade emerging. It is an Italian symbol that had its origin in the Etruscan civilization and was passed on to ancient Rome, representing law, power and governance.

During the first half of 20th century, the fasces became the symbol of National Fascist Party of Italy (origin of the term [i][[fascist|fascism]][/i]).

title: toyota_sprinter_trueno
body:
The Toyota Sprinter Trueno is a small, lightweight coupe introduced by Toyota in 1983 as part of the fifth generation Toyota Corolla lineup. The insider-chassis code of "AE86" depicts the 1600 cc rear-wheel drive model from the range. The Levin has fixed-headlights, and the Trueno has retractable headlights, both could be hatchback or coupe. The export model name Corolla covers both variations. 

The car is best known for its incredible handling characteristic, which leads into it being frequently used in various [[drifting|drift]] [[racing]] tournaments.

This tag also covers the AE85 (sold as the Toyota Corolla Levin, Toyota Sprinter Trueno or Toyota Corolla DX), likewise a rear-wheel drive sports coupe, manufactured by Toyota from 1983-1987. While the AE85 shares its chassis and basic design with the famous AE86, the AE85 was designed for economy and differs mainly in its engine, compared to the AE86, which was designed for performance.

The white and black color variant (informally known as the "panda" Trueno) is most known as [[Fujiwara Takumi]]'s [[fujiwara takumi's toyota trueno ae86|'Tofu Delivery' car]] from the [[Initial D]] series, while [[Takeuchi Itsuki]] purchases an AE85 Levin, mistaken for an AE86. Later on, a young man by the name of [[Inui Shinji]] appears, driving a notchback late-model Trueno.

h4. See also

* "Wikipedia: Toyota Corolla Levin and Toyota Sprinter Trueno":[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toyota_Corolla_Levin_and_Toyota_Sprinter_Trueno]
* "Wikipedia: Toyota AE86":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toyota_AE86

title: u.n._spacy
body:
The [b]U.N. Spacy[/b] (United Nations [[Space]] Navy) is the fictional [[military]] arm of the Earth U.N. Government (地球統合政府 [i]"Chikyuu Tougou Seifu"[/i]) in the [[Macross]] Japanese anime series.

The organization's name is derived from words [b]SPAC[/b]E and NAV[b]Y[/b], therefore, combining them to make the word [b]SPACY[/b]. 

In the Macross chronology it was established after 1999 by the successor to the modern [[United Nations]] in order to defend Earth from a possible attack by hostile [[alien]]s.

However, from 1999 to 2008 the U.N. Spacy was also involved in the [[Macross Zero|U.N. Wars]] conflict, fighting against a human [[Anti-U.N.]] faction opposed to the formation of the worldwide U.N. government. 

A year later (2009) the U.N. Spacy was involved in the subsequent [[Choujikuu Yousai Macross|Space War I]], defending our planet from an hostile extraterrestrial race called the [[Zentradi]]. Later operations of the U.N. Spacy expanded into interstellar colonization and general peacekeeping of off-world Earth settlements.

At the time of the Zentradi invasion, the U.N. Spacy's assets included military bases on Earth, the [[Moon]] and [[Mars (planet)|]], squadrons of variable fighters and other [[mecha]], several capital [[spacecraft]] in orbit and the repaired SDF-1 [i]Macross[/i] on South Ataria Island, the flagship of the United Nations Spacy.

The U.N. Spacy was succeeded by the [b]New U.N. Spacy[/b] ([[N.U.N.S.]]).  

In the [[ROBOTECH]] western adaptation the U.N. Spacy is reimagined as the actual space navy component of the [b]Robotech Defense Force (R.D.F.)[/b].

title: retsu_kaioh
body:
Supporting character from [[Grappler Baki]].

Retsu is a Chinese martial artist and a kenpo master, being one of the expert martial artist who held the prestigious title of Kaioh (lit. "Sea King") for his prowress. While he is proud of "4,000 years of Chinese martial arts" history and is eager to prove its prowress to the world though underground fighting tournament, he also recognise other strong-willed fighters and often befriending them.

[spoiler]He is later killed by [[Miyamoto Musashi (baki)|]] in battle, and his severed right arm was later grafted onto [[Orochi Katsumi]] as a replacement for his own right arm that were lost during his fight with [[Pickle (grappler baki)|]].[/spoiler]

title: triceratops_fist
body:
A [[martial arts]] technique used by [[Hanma Baki]] from [[Grappler Baki]], first conceived during his fight against the prehistoric caveman [[Pickle (grappler_baki)|]].

To use this technique, the user takes one step forward, lowers their upper body, and juts their fists forward, with one fist above and one below their head somewhat akin to a [[triceratops]]' horns. With this stance, the user is capable of parrying the opponent's attack, as well as performing a powerful charge at the same time.

Parodies of this stance often have the silhouette of a [[triceratops]] behind the user, in reference to when this technique was used for the first time by Baki.

title: defibrillator
body:
A [b]Defibrillator[/b] is medical device that sends an electric pulse or shock to the heart. 

Despite what you might see in movies and TV, defibrillators do not send an electric shock to restart your heart if it stops beating but the opposite, as the device stops your heart to help normalize your regular heartbeat if it's beating irregularly or too fast.

title: stance_(vehicle)
body:
A style of modified [[ground vehicle]]s that lowers ride height and typically includes other aesthetic modifications such as widebody fender flares and negative camber on the wheels. Stance styling is primarily inspired by [[drifting|drift]] cars, though it usually takes features applied for practical performance reasons and exaggerates them for purely stylistic purposes.

Stance is usually applied to Japanese [[car]]s, but there are also stance communities centered around other types of vehicles including [[pickup truck]]s and [[muscle car]]s.

body:
A twin-engine narrow-body airliner manufactured by American aerospace manufacturer [[Boeing]], designed as a competitor to the Airbus A320neo.

The latest development of the [[boeing 737|737]] family, it features more fuel efficient [[jet engine|engines]] with noise-reducing chevrons, redesigned winglets, as well as the [b]Maneuvering Characteristics Augmentation System[/b] ("MCAS":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maneuvering_Characteristics_Augmentation_System).

It has also had a troubled history involving two crashes in "2018":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lion_Air_Flight_610 and "2019":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethiopian_Airlines_Flight_302 caused by sudden activation of the MCAS which killed 346 people, and an "incident in early 2024":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alaska_Airlines_Flight_1282 where a door plug on the side of the plane blew off mid flight.

title: masters_of_the_air
body:
[b]Masters of the Air[/b] is a 2024 American [[war]] drama miniseries created by John Shiban and John Orloff for Apple TV+. It is based on the 2007 book of the same name by Donald L. Miller and follows the actions of the 100th Bomb Group, a Boeing B-17 Flying Fortress heavy bomber unit in the Eighth United States Air Force in eastern England during [[World War II]]. 

The series serves as a companion to [[Band of Brothers]] (2001) and [[The Pacific]] (2010). It is the first series to be produced by Apple Studios in cooperation with Playtone and Amblin Television and stars Austin Butler, Callum Turner and Anthony Boyle as part of an ensemble cast. The series consists of nine episodes. Masters of the Air premiered on January 26, 2024 and received positive reception.

title: 3ldkm
body:
Originally released on his livedoor blog, from between February 6th to March 10th, 2008, before being fully corrected and finished by March 18th, [b]3LDKM[/b] is a largely [[4koma]]-based webcomic created by [[bkub]]. The series follows a man named [[Tsuneda]] who moves into an apartment that comes with a robot maid named [[Fumimi]].

It was entered into the 8th Dengeki Comic Grand Prix in the Shounen Division, where it ended up winning the "Excellence Prize":[http://blog.livedoor.jp/bkub/archives/51196689.html]. This would later lead to his serialized debut later that year, with [[Super Elegant]] in October. Following its first run, bkub would properly cap off 3LDKM's first season on October 11th, with him posting about his new series on G's Festival! later on the 27th.

Later on, as bkub "transitioned":[http://blog.livedoor.jp/bkub/archives/51411970.html] from his livedoor blog to Twitter and his rc2 page, 3LDKM would have a second season, running from August 10th, 2009, and later a third season, coinciding with bkub getting a new handle on Twitter on October 18th, 2012, would run from October 20th to October 25th, 2012, released on Twitter via Twitpic and on Pixiv.

title: harlock
body:
A character from the [[Harlock Saga]] series created by [[Matsumoto Leiji]] in the 70s.

[b]Captain Harlock[/b] is a legendary [[Space Pirate]] and adventurer who travels across [[space]] in his [[spacecraft|ship]], [i]The [[Arcadia]][/i]. He is [[Ooyama Toshiro]]'s best friend.

Harlock is the archetypical romantic hero, a space pirate with an individualist philosophy of life. He is as noble as he is taciturn, rebellious, stoically fighting against totalitarian regimes, whether they be earthborn or [[alien]]. In his own words, he "fight(s) for no one's sake... only for something deep in (his) heart". He does not fear [[death]], and is sometimes seen wearing clothing with the number 42 on it. In Japanese culture, the number 42 is associated with death (the numbers, pronounced separately as "four two", sound like the words "shi ni"—meaning "to death").

In [[real life]] during 1979 the character of Harlock won the first annual [[Animage]] Grand Prix ever for favorite anime character.

Harlock also appears as a sidekick in the manga series [[Gun Frontier (western)]].

title: cockpit
body:
A [b]cockpit[/b] (also called [b]flight deck[/b] in big airplanes) is the area, usually near the front of a vehicle, from which its [[pilot]] controls it. 

Most modern cockpits are enclosed, except on some small [[aircraft]], and cockpits on large airliners are also physically separated from the cabin. From the cockpit an aircraft is controlled on the ground and in the air.

Most [[mecha]] also contain cockpits for a human operator.

title: the_fantasie_of_a_stepmother
body:
A 2019-to-Present shoujo fantasy Korean webtoon written by Spice&Kitty and illustrated by ORKA.  The English releases of the series is split between the webtoon released by Tapas under the name [i]The Fantasie of a Stepmother[/i] and the physical volumes released by Seven Seas under the name [i] A Stepmother's Märchen[/i].

The series follows Shuri von Neuschwanstein, a young lady from a poor family of low nobility.  Forced into a marriage by her family with a man of high nobility at the age of 14, things take a difficult turn when she is left widowed at the age of 16.   Shocking everyone, her husband left her as head of the estate in his will.  With everyone seemingly expecting her to fail, she struggles and perseveres for 7 years to keep the promise she made to raise her stepchildren Jeremy, Elias, Rachel, and Leon.  Despite strained relationships with the stepchildren, she succeeds in seeing the eldest son Jeremy come of age, become the new head of the estate, and be about to marry. Just before the wedding though, Jeremy's fiance tells her that Jeremy does not want her at the wedding. Feeling slighted, but relieved to finally be over with it all, Shuri chooses grant the wish she believes her stepchildren have and depart the household for good.  The next thing she knows she's startled awake back in bed as she remembers that her carriage had just been attacked by bandits.  Not sure what is going on, she is shocked to learn she has somehow traveled back to the day of her husband's funeral.  With the knowledge that she now has, she sees this as a second chance to make different choices in life.

[[Elsword]] character. A former Demon Lord who was betrayed by one of her vassals and stripped of her power. title: dororo_(tezuka)
body:
A dark [[fantasy]] manga written by [[Tezuka Osamu]], first published in 1967 and later adapted into anime in 1969 and 2019, as well as a live-action movie in 2007 and several [[video game]]s.

Set in the Sengoku period, the story revolves around a ronin named [[hyakkimaru (dororo)|Hyakkimaru]], who traveled with the orphaned thief [[Dororo (character)|Dororo]] to retrieve his missing body parts. They were split and scattered into 48 pieces after his birth due to his father ([[Daigo Kagemitsu]]) forging a pact with demons to gave him enough power to conquer the land. Hyakkimaru's job is to kill the demons who currently hold each part, and in the process try to fight his budding bloodlust and cynicism from taking over his common sense.

title: nanako_sos
body:
"Nanako SOS is a seinen manga series created by [[Azuma Hideo]] which ran in Popcorn and Just Comic (both published by Kobunsha) from April 1980 to July 1986. The series was adapted into 39-episode anime TV series produced by Kokusai Eiga which aired on the Fuji Television network from April 2, 1983 to December 24, 1983. Azuma created additional manga stories which ran in Azuma Magazine from July 2001 to July 2004.

Enoki Films held the North American distribution rights of TV series, under the name Nana the Supergirl, though the series was never aired in North America. The TV series has also aired in Italy, France, Germany and Russia." [1]

title: horizon_(apex_legends)
body:
Playable legend in [[Apex Legends]], added to the game in season 7. A scientist who was left for dead at a black hole, and found that 87 years had passed on her homeworld after she escaped.

Horizon has [[short hair|short]] [[brown hair|brown]]/[[orange hair]] (depending on the depiction) and [[blue eyes]]. Her default outfit consists of slim blue [[spacesuit]] with a pair of [[goggles on head|goggles on her head]]. While she was born on Psamanthe, she is of Scottish descent and speaks with a Scottish accent.

She is [[Newton Somers]]' mother, and her main motivation for remaining in the games is to return to her original time period to reunite with him. Due to her betrayal, she has a strong animosity against both [[Ashleigh Reid]] and her simulacrum [[Ash (titanfall 2)|]]. Horizon is heavily associated with [[Olympus (apex legends)|]], having been released in the same season. Her heirloom weapon is the [[Gravity Maw]].

Horizon is voiced by "Elle Newlands":[https://www.behindthevoiceactors.com/Elle-Newlands/] in English and "Aruga Yukiko":[https://www.behindthevoiceactors.com/Yukiko-Aruga/] in Japanese.

title: mira_(kendeshi)
body:
Mira (ミラ) is the protagonist of the series [[Kenja no Deshi wo Nanoru Kenja]].  She is depicted as a young girl with [[very long hair|very long]] [[silver hair]] and [[blue eyes]].

Mira is the female appearance of the young working man Sakamori Kagami's player avatar in the VRMMORPG Ark Earth Online.  Kagami's avatar, Danblf Gandador, is normally a wizened old man with long white hair and long beard that he based on famous fantasy wizards.  While toying with the appearance editor and seeing what he could create for a female appearance, Kagami blacked out and awoke as his avatar with the female appearance he had just created.

The name Mira is derived from the English word Mirror (Mirā, ミラー, in Japanese), and is taken from Kagami's name sounding the same as the Japanese word for mirror, Kagami (鏡).

title: cao_cao
body:
[b]Cao Cao[/b] (曹操), courtesy name [b]Mengde[/b] (孟德), was a Chinese statesman, warlord, and poet who rose to power towards the end of the [[Han Dynasty|Eastern Han dynasty]] and became the effective head of the Han central government during that period. He laid the foundation for what was to become the state of [[Cao Wei]] (220–265), established by his son and successor [[Cao Pi]], who ended the Eastern Han dynasty and inaugurated the [[Romance of the Three Kingdoms|Three Kingdoms period]] (220–280). 

Cao Cao rose to prominence in the 190s during which he recruited his own followers, formed his own army, and set up a base in Yan Province (covering parts of present-day Henan and Shandong). In 196, he received [[Emperor Xian]], the figurehead Han sovereign who was previously held hostage by other warlords such as [[Dong Zhuo]], [[Li Jue]], and [[Guo Si]]. After he established the new imperial capital in Xuchang, Emperor Xian and the central government came under his direct control, but he still paid nominal allegiance to the emperor. Throughout the 190s, Cao Cao actively waged wars in central China against rival warlords such as [[Lu bu|Lü Bu]], [[Yuan Shu]], and [[Zhang Xiu]], eliminating all of them. Following his triumph over the warlord [[Yuan Shao]] at the Battle of Guandu in 200, Cao Cao launched a series of campaigns against Yuan Shao's sons and allies over the following seven years, defeated them, and unified much of northern China under his control. In 208, shortly after Emperor Xian appointed him as Imperial Chancellor, he embarked on an expedition to gain a foothold in southern China, but was defeated by the allied forces of the warlords [[Sun Quan]], [[Liu Bei]], and [[Liu Qi]] at the decisive Battle of Red Cliffs.

His subsequent attempts over the following years to annex the lands south of the Yangtze River never proved successful. Cao Cao died in Luoyang in March 220 and was succeeded by his son Cao Pi, who accepted the abdication of Emperor Xian in November 220 and established the state of Cao Wei to replace the Eastern Han dynasty. This marked the transition from the Eastern Han dynasty to the Six Dynasties period. After taking the throne, Cao Pi granted his father the posthumous title "Emperor Wu" ("Martial Emperor") and the temple name "Taizu" ("Grand Ancestor").

body: The Dark Knight is a 2008 superhero film directed by Christopher Nolan from a screenplay co-written with his brother Jonathan. Based on the [[DC Comics]] superhero [[Batman]], it is the sequel to [[Batman Begins]] (2005) and the second installment in The Dark Knight trilogy. The plot follows the vigilante Batman, police lieutenant [[James Gordon]], and district attorney [[Harvey Dent]], who form an alliance to dismantle organized crime in Gotham City. Their efforts are derailed by the Joker, an anarchistic mastermind who seeks to test how far Batman will go to save the city from chaos. The ensemble cast includes [[Christian Bale]], Michael Caine, Heath Ledger, Gary Oldman, Aaron Eckhart, Maggie Gyllenhaal, and [[Morgan Freeman]].

title: maou_no_ore_ga_dorei_elf_wo_yome_ni_shitanda_ga_dou_medereba_ii?
body:
The original title roughly means, "As the Demon King, what would be the right way to love my elf slave bride?"
Official English Title: "An Archdemon's Dilemma: How to Love Your Elf Bride"

A light novel by Fuminori Teshima and illustrated by C O M T A.

The sorcerer Zagan spends his fortune to buy [[Nephelia]] ("Nephy"), a white-haired elven slave (rumored to make good magic sacrifices), after falling in love with her at first sight.  His dark magic terrifies her, as does the torture device-riddled abandoned castle he's been squatting in, convincing her that he's more interested in torturing her than love, especially since he's too antisocial to string together a sentence.  Also, The Church is convinced he's the flesh-reaping serial murdering sorcerer that targets virgins, and has sent holy knights to bring him to justice, led by a [s]side romantic interest[/s] sword maiden he once saved.

Hilarity ensues.

Not to be confused with [[Isekai Maou To Shoukan Shoujo no Dorei Majutsu]], the OTHER light novel about a Maou with a busty elf slave waifu.
